**Safety Notes:**

- **Slippery underfoot:** The ground is saturated after more than usual autumn rain, so many parts are muddy and waterlogged. Also the ground is covered with autumn leaves which obscure minor paths and and other features.
Please take great care. Wear only O-shoes with good cleats. DO NOT wear flat soled trainers.

- **Dangerous high crags and earth banks:**Marked as**uncrossable** using a thick purple line along the top edge. Some crags are 10m high!

- **River crossings:** Advice will be given on the Start line. There are 3 options:
Foot bridges (marked on the map as a crossing point). Unaffected by water levels.- Easier fording points (marked on the map as a crossing point). Depending on water levels a hand rail rope may be fixed to trees on both banks.- When water levels are low, it is possible to ford at many points. Cross safely at your discretion.

